df.sketch.howto("Make time series analysis for CO2")

# Import necessary libraries
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

# Create a time series plot for CO2
plt.plot(_['Year'], _['CO2'])
plt.xlabel('Year')
plt.ylabel('CO2 (ppm)')
plt.title('CO2 Time Series')
plt.show()

# Calculate summary statistics for CO2
print("Summary Statistics for CO2:")
print("Mean:", _.CO2.mean())
print("Median:", _.CO2.median())
print("Standard Deviation:", _.CO2.std())
print("Minimum:", _.CO2.min())
print("Maximum:", _.CO2.max())

# Calculate the correlation between CO2 and Year
print("Correlation between CO2 and Year:", _.CO2.corr(_.Year))

# Create a boxplot for CO2
plt.boxplot(_['CO2'])
plt.ylabel('CO2 (ppm)')
plt.title('CO2 Boxplot')
plt.show()

    print("Correlation is relatively strong")
elif correlation_ch4 > 1.0:
    print("Correlation is strong")
elif correlation_ch4 < -0.5:
    print('Correlation is negative')
else:
    print('Correlation is weak or negligible')

In [68]:
# Calculate the proportion of each greenhouse gas to the total
df['CO2_prop'] = df['CO2'] / df['Total']
df['CH4_prop'] = df['CH4'] / df['Total']
df['N2O_prop'] = df['N2O'] / df['Total']
df['CFCs_prop'] = df['CFCs'] / df['Total']
df['HCFCs_prop'] = df['HCFCs'] / df['Total']
df['HFCs_prop'] = df['HFCs'] / df['Total']

# Calculate the proportion of each greenhouse gas to the CO2-eq (ppm)
df['CO2eq_prop'] = df['CO2-eq (ppm)'] / df['Total']

# Sort the dataframe by the highest proportion of each gas to the total
df.sort_values(by=['CO2_prop', 'CH4_prop', 'N2O_prop', 'CFCs_prop', 'HCFCs_prop', 'HFCs_prop'], ascending=False, inplace=True)

# Print the top 3 contributors to the total
print("Top 3 contributors to the total:")
print(df[['CO2', 'CH4', 'N2O', 'CFCs', 'HCFCs', 'HFCs']].head(3))

# Print the top 3 contributors to the CO2-eq (ppm)
print("Top 3 contributors to the CO2-eq (ppm):")
print(df[['CO2-eq (ppm)', 'CO2eq_prop']].head(3))
